title: Bastar cop dies in encounter with Maoists

description: CBI filed chargesheet against seven suspects in connection with looting of arms and ammunition from an India Reserve Battalion (IRB) in Manipur's Bishnupur district during the ethnic strife which broke out in the state last year. CBI filed chargesheet before court of chief judicial magistrate, Kamrup (Metro), in Guwahati in Assam. Supreme Court had transferred all CBI cases from Manipur to Assam last August.
title: Chargesheet filed against 7 in Manipur arms loot case
On Wed, Navy to commission first squadron of Seahawk copters

description: Congress leadership is considering a change in the Himachal chief minister's post before the Lok Sabha elections. The party is reluctant but will review the issue. Sukhvinder Singh Sukhu is facing pressure from disgruntled MLAs and the party is concerned about the rival camp and BJP's objective.
title: Congress to review HP issue, but CM change unlikely

description: PM Narendra Modi is set to embark on a three-day visit to five states, including Telangana, Tamil Nadu, Odisha, West Bengal, and Bihar. During the trip, he will dedicate and lay the foundation for various development projects. The schedule includes the inauguration of projects worth over Rs 56,000 crore in Adilabad, Telangana, on Monday, followed by a visit to BHAVINI in Kalpakkam, Tamil Nadu.
title: PM Modi to launch projects in 5 states in 3 days

description: A day after PM Modi slammed RJD & Congress on 'parivaarvad', RJD chief Lalu launched a scathing attack on Modi at the 'Jan Vishwas Maharally' in Patna on Sunday. "He (Modi) accuses us of doing dynastic politics. What can we do if Modi does not have a family of his own?" Lalu said, adding "Modi is not even a true Hindu" as he didn't shave head on the demise of his parent.
title: At opposition rally, RJD chief Lalu hits back at PM Modi on 'dynasty'

description: Pragya Thakur, BJP MP from Bhopal, has been dropped from the Lok Sabha candidates' list for the 2024 elections. Known for making polarizing remarks, she acknowledged that PM Modi may not have liked some of her statements but reiterated her commitment to the party's goal of making India a 'Vishwa Guru.'
title: 'Perhaps PM Modi didn’t like my opinion, can’t help it': Pragya Thakur

description: Amit Shah highlights the Modi administration's relentless and uncompromising commitment against narco-trafficking, resulting in increased drug seizures. The Centre aims to build an invincible anti-narcotics apparatus under the guidance of PM Modi, ensuring a drug-free society and leaving behind a valuable drug-free legacy.
title: Amit Shah: Government's anti-drug steps behind rise in seizures
Sparks fly between Shinde's Sena and BJP ahead of release of LS lists

description: Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud and top judges of Supreme Court are in the process of devising a mechanism to objectively identify 'super performers' among judicial officers in trial courts. CJI said, "Why should a super performer be equated with a good judicial officer? Why should a good judicial officer be equated with a non-performing judicial officer? We must find a mechanism by which performers get motivated through additional incentives."
title: SC plans to incentivise 'super performer' trial court judges

description: FM Nirmala Sitharaman will inaugurate a conference of GST enforcement chiefs on Monday and the meeting will discuss combating evasion, among other issues. The one day conference will also discuss combating fake invoicing. It will address this primary form of GST evasion and strategise effective methods to combat it collaboratively.
title: Evasion fight: FM Sitharaman to meet GST enforcement chiefs

description: Walmart-owned Flipkart on Sunday launched its UPI handle in partnership with Axis Bank. The UPI offering will initially be available for Android users. Flipkart is taking competition to the doors of its rival Amazon which runs its payment vertical Amazon Pay besides other payment firms like Paytm, PhonePe and Google Pay.
title: Flipkart joins UPI race, 2nd Walmart co

description: It's that time of year when taxpayers under the old tax regime - mostly the salaried class - rush in to invest that extra amount to help them save some taxes under section 80C of the Income Tax Act. The tax saving options available to taxpayers are: Equity Linked Savings Schemes (ELSS), National Savings Certificate (NSC), PPF, NPS, fixed deposits (FDs), life insurance plans and a few others.
title: ELSS edge out tax saving options

description: The BJP has delayed announcing candidates for over 100 Lok Sabha constituencies, including 29 in Uttar Pradesh, leading to uncertainty for sitting MPs, including prominent figures like Union Minister V K Singh, Maneka Gandhi, Varun Gandhi, and Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh. There are speculations about possible replacements for some candidates due to issues such as non-adherence to the party line or controversies.
title: Singh, Gandhi on waitlist as names for 100 BJP seats on hold

description: Pawan Singh withdrew as BJP candidate for Asansol Lok Sabha. Bhojpuri stars Manoj Tiwary, Ravi Kishan, and Nirahua remain BJP MPs. Shatrughan Sinha won seat on TMC ticket in 2022 bypoll. Singh starred in Pratigya, Loha Pahalwan, and Saiyaan Superstar.
title: No 'Fab 4', but BJP still has 'Big 3' of Bhojpuri cineverse

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi has donated Rs 2,000 to the BJP fund ahead of the Lok Sabha polls and encouraged others to contribute for nation-building. He made the donation through the NaMo app and shared a screenshot of the receipt. This call for donations follows the recent Supreme Court ruling declaring the electoral bonds scheme unconstitutional, with the BJP emphasizing the scheme's introduction for transparency in electoral funding.
title: PM Modi contributes Rs 2,000 to BJP fund, seeks donations

description: Calcutta High Court Judge Justice Abhijit Gangopadhyay, previously involved in a courtroom spat where the state's advocate general claimed he would receive a BJP ticket for the Lok Sabha election, has announced his resignation from the judiciary to enter politics. Due to retire officially in August, he expressed a desire to combat corruption on a broader platform.
title: Judge in Calcutta HC row set to quit law, tipped to join BJP

description: Bhojpuri singer Pawan Singh withdraws candidacy for Asansol Lok Sabha constituency due to attacks from TMC and criticism from BJP's state unit. Opposition arises from BJP ranks and social media backlash. Former Tripura governor urges party leadership to rethink Singh's nomination.
title: 'Lollipop' in hot water: Asansol BJP candidate backs out of poll
Was immunity in JMM bribery case right call? SC to rule today

description: The share of imported coal in overall consumption in the country has come down to 19.3% in Apr-Dec of the financial year ending March 31 from 21% in the previous corresponding period, translating into Rs 82,264 crore worth of forex savings, the coal ministry said.
title: India saves Rs 82k crore forex outgo on coal imports

description: Ola Electric, the IPO-bound pure-play Indian EV manufacturer, has emerged as the most prolific patent publisher in the country among its peers in the 2022-23 period. With 205 patents published in the EV and EV-related technologies space with the Indian patents office, it tops the table in this segment of intellectual property rights race.
title: Ola Electric races ahead with 205 EV patents

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai is under growing pressure following the series of gaffes and biases demonstrated by its recently launched generative AI tool Gemini. Some have even begun calling for his resignation. Ben Thompson, author at technology analysis firm Stratechery, writes that Google needs a transformation of its culture, similar to the way Satya Nadella did at Microsoft.
title: Sundar Pichai under pressure after AI chatbot gaffes

description: Train drivers watching cricket caused a fatal collision that killed 14 in Vizianagaram, Andhra Pradesh. New safety systems will detect distractions to ensure focused pilots. Railway committed to safety and investigating root causes. Previous accidents include Coromandel Express crash with 296 deaths.
title: Pilots were watching cricket when trains crashed: Railway minister

description: After hitting new life-high levels in the previous week, the Sensex and Nifty are expected to continue their northward movement this week on the back of strong buying in blue chips while mid and small-cap stocks could see some correction in the holiday-shortened week. In the previous week, the Sensex on Saturday (in a special sessions) closed just a tad off the 74K mark, at 73,806 points, while Nifty was at 22,378 points.
title: Blue chip demand to help Sensex scale new peaks

description: Seven people lost their lives in two weather-related accidents in J&K on Sunday as heavy rain lashed the region, bringing temperatures down to negative in the upper reaches. According to officials, a woman and her three minor daughters died when the roof of their house collapsed in Reasi district of Jammu division. Two others were injured and rushed to hospital for treatment.
title: 7 killed in rain-related accidents in Jammu & Kashmir

description: The parents of missing Indian Navy sailor Sahil Verma are urging for a CBI (Central Bureau of Investigation) inquiry into his mysterious disappearance from a naval ship on Feb 27. The family has sought intervention from PM Narendra Modi, Defence Minister Rajnath Singh, Home Minister Amit Shah, and J&K LG Manoj Sinha for Sahil's safe return.
title: Parents of missing Navy sailor demand CBI probe, seek PM’s help

description: Vaibhav Gupta from Kanpur emerges as the winner of Indian Idol 14, impressing judges and celebrity guests. He receives Rs 25 lakh, a car. Mentored by Kumar Sanu, Shreya Ghoshal, and Vishal Dadlani, Vaibhav showcases his talent among the top 6 finalists. Here's what the winner has to say.
title: Kanpur’s Vaibhav Gupta wins Indian Idol 14 trophy

description: Captain Meg Lanning's fifty and a cunning spell of left-arm spin by Jess Jonassen drove Delhi Capitals to a slick 25-run victory over Gujarat Giants in their Women's Premier League match on Sunday. The defeat was Giants fourth on the bounce this season.
title: WPL: Lanning, bowlers help DC reclaim top spot

description: Italy and India enhance their relationship through a strategic partnership, focusing on defense collaboration, connectivity projects, and addressing global challenges. The Italian G7 presidency aligns with India's G20 priorities, strengthening the partnership between the two countries.
title: Defence ties with India key to Indo-Pacific stability: Italian envoy
'Bullies don't give ...': Jaishankar's veiled shot at Maldives prez

description: Pakistan's newly-elected Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif made a mistake during his victory speech in the National Assembly. Instead of thanking his party members for electing him as the Prime Minister, he mistakenly thanked them for choosing him as the leader of the opposition. Shehbaz's rival Omar Ayub Khan, whom jailed former PM Imran Khan's Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) backed, received only 92 votes.
title: New Pak PM Shehbaz Sharif calls himself 'leader of opposition'

description: Indian security agencies seized a consignment bound for Karachi suspected to contain 'dual-use consignment'. Pakistan's foreign ministry protested, condemning India's high-handedness and violation of international norms. Private entities are pursuing action. The seized CNC machine is included in the Wassenaar Arrangement.
title: 'Unjustified': Pakistan reacts to India seizing 'military-grade items'

description: Legendary India batter Sunil Gavaskar has come out in defence of Shreyas Iyer after the right-handed batter was denied a central contract for the 2023/24 season by the BCCI, pointing out that he had featured in the Ranji Trophy before the ongoing Test series against England began. Iyer and Ishan Kishan were not included in the 30-member BCCI Central Contracts list running from October 1, 2023 to September 30, 2024, with the governing body saying the duo were not recommended for the annual retainership.
title: Gavaskar comes out in support of Shreyas Iyer

description: The Indian Navy will commission its first squadron of MH-60R Seahawk helicopters armed with a range of weapons and advanced capabilities. The squadron, commissioned as INAS 334, will be based in Kochi. The helicopters will significantly enhance India's maritime prowess and counter the increasing presence of Chinese submarines.
title: Navy to commission 1st squadron of submarine-hunting MH-60R Seahawk choppers on March 6

description: Pawan Singh withdrew as BJP candidate for Asansol Lok Sabha. BJP's Manoj Tiwary, Ravi Kishan, and Dinesh Lal Yadav 'Nirahua' remain as candidates. Pawan Singh could have faced Shatrughan Sinha from TMC. Bhojpuri stars were not successful in their first attempts.
title: Bhojpuri actor-singer Pawan Singh changes poll tune overnight
PM Modi, ministers discuss 5-yr action plan for 'Viksit Bharat 2047' vision

description: The INDIA bloc kicked off its campaign for the Lok Sabha elections in Bihar's capital. Rahul Gandhi, Mallikarjun Kharge, Lalu Prasad Yadav, Tejashvi Yadav, and Akhilesh Yadav shared the stage at the Jan Vishwas Maha Rally. Kharge accused PM Modi of spreading lies and destroying the country. Nitish Kumar was criticized for his recent change of heart.
title: INDIA bloc leaders sound poll bugle at Patna rally

description: RJD president Lalu Prasad attacked PM Modi on Sunday, accusing him of not being a true Hindu and attacking dynasty politics. Speaking at the Jan Vishwas Maha Rally in Patna, Lalu lambasted the PM for criticising "parivarvad (dynastic rule)" in politics and spreading hatred. Known for pulling no punches, the RJD supremo said, "What can we do if PM does not have a family of his own? He keeps bragging about the Ram temple."
title: 'Why didn't you shave your head?': Lalu's odd attack against PM
'Does he not feel ashamed?': Lalu Yadav slams Bihar CM Nitish

description: Swashbuckling keeper-batter Rishabh Pant was on Sunday seen having fun playing marbles with kids. Rishabh is all set to return to professional cricket in the upcoming season of IPL. Delhi Capitals' Director of Cricket, Sourav Ganguly earlier hinted that Rishabh may not be directly pushed into wicketkeeping in the IPL.
title: Watch: Pant's 'Goli' time with kids ahead of IPL return

description: The world-famous Blue Lagoon and the nearby town of Grindavik in Iceland have been evacuated due to intense seismic activity indicating a possible volcanic eruption. The magma depth is around four kilometers. Operations in the Blue Lagoon remain closed until at least the end of Saturday for a reassessment of the situation.
title: Iceland evacuates Blue Lagoon amid fears of 'imminent' eruption

description: Farmers are called to join the protest in Delhi on March 6 and participate in the 'rail roko' protest on March 10. The ongoing agitation at Shambhu and Khanauri border points is supported by farmers from Punjab and Haryana. The fight for rights continues.
title: Farmer leaders call for nationwide protests, 'rail roko' on March 10

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi has criticised Prime Minister Narendra Modi's financial policies, claiming that India's unemployment rate is twice that of Pakistan. Gandhi also argued that the government's policies have led to the decline of small and medium enterprises in the country, resulting in a worsening economic and job situation. He further highlighted that India is even performing worse than Bhutan and Bangladesh in these areas.
title: India's unemplyoment rate double that of Pak, says Rahul Gandhi

description: BJP leader and former Himachal Pradesh CM, Jairam Thakur, has alerted party workers to be prepared for potential developments in the coming days. This implies a potential change of leadership in the state, as the ruling Congress party faces challenges in maintaining its unity. Thakur's statement follows the abrupt departure of Congress ministers Rohit Thakur and Jagat Singh Negi from a cabinet meeting, following heated arguments.
title: Jai Ram Thakur targets Cong, says anything can happen in coming days in Himachal
Rising militancy, inflation: Many challenges await new Shehbaz Sharif govt in Pakistan

description: With England losing the ongoing Test series to India, former captain Michael Vaughan believes the Ben Stokes-led side haven't been able to win their last three series in the format due to the failure of their batting department.
title: 'England's failure to win last three Test series is due to...': Vaughan

description: Flipkart has launched Flipkart UPI, a new payment service to compete with Amazon Pay, Paytm, and other UPI-based apps in India. Flipkart UPI allows users to make online payments, pay local vendors, friends, and family, make bill payments, and more.
title: Flipkart launches this Paytm, Amazon Pay-rival: How to get started

description: Yemen's Iran-backed Houthis vow to persist in targeting British ships in the Gulf of Aden. The US military confirmed the sinking of the UK-owned vessel Rubymar, struck by a Yemeni Houthi anti-ship ballistic missile. Houthi-led government condemns Britain's actions in Gaza, disrupting global shipping. US and Britain retaliate against Houthi targets in Yemen.
title: ‘Whoever harms Yemen ...’: Houthis vows to sink more British ships

description: Jill Biden, amid her husband's reelection campaign, criticizes Donald Trump's treatment of women, branding him as dangerous. She targets Black and Latino communities in Arizona, Nevada, and Wisconsin, emphasizing Trump's perceived threats. Biden leads the "Women for Biden-Harris" coalition, rallying female voters against Trump. Roe v Wade's impact boosts Democratic support among women.
title: 'Trump is dangerous to women': Jill Biden takes center stage

description: Former union health minister Harsh Vardhan steps away from electoral politics after being dropped from BJP's candidate list. He plans to return to his ENT clinic and continue his work against tobacco and substance abuse, climate change, and teaching sustainable lifestyles.
title: 'My ENT clinic awaits my return:' Harsh Vardhan quits politics

description: Aakash Chopra, the ex-Indian opener, believes that the forthcoming IPL presents an ideal chance for Ishan Kishan to rejuvenate his career, especially in the wake of his exclusion from the BCCI central contract list for 2023-2024. "Ishan Kishan will be hungry, as he has not got a central contract. This is the only thing he is playing. What else is he playing?" Chopra said in his YouTube video.
title: 'If you make IPL your own...': Chopra on Ishan

description: The US spacecraft Odysseus entered a dormant state as the lunar night began. The Intuitive Machines plans to wake it up after three weeks. Odysseus spacecraft sent a final transmission featuring the lunar surface and a distant shadowed Earth crescent, marking the first company in Nasa's commercial lunar delivery program.
title: US Moon lander captures Earth's 'crescent' in parting shot

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) president Uddhav Thackeray criticized the BJP after it unveiled its initial list of 195 candidates for the Lok Sabha elections. Uddhav expressed surprise that'veteran leader and party loyalist Nitin Gadkari's name was not on the BJP's list, while Kripashankar Singh, the accused in the disproportionate assets case, was on the first list.
title: Not Gadkari but graft accused Kripa on BJP's first list: Uddhav

description: Relatives of the passengers who went missing on Malaysia Airlines flight MH370 a decade ago are demanding a fresh search. They are struggling to find closure without any trace of the plane. The flight, carrying 239 people, disappeared on March 8, 2014, while traveling from Kuala Lumpur to Beijing. The plane has never been found despite years of search operations, which is considered the largest in aviation history.
title: A decade after MH370's disappearance, families seek fresh search

description: Gujarat Titans’ uncapped wicketkeeper-batter Robin Minz met with a bike accident and is currently under observation. Last year, Minz had become the first player from the Adivasi community to be a part of the IPL when Titans’ picked him for Rs 3.6 crore in the player auction.
title: IPL: GT's Rs 3.60 cr new signing meets with accident

description: NCP leader Surpriya Sule showcases badminton skills in Baramati campaign. Video goes viral. Sunetra Pawar may compete. Seat-sharing formula for Lok Sabha Elections 2024 in Maha Vikas Aghadi alliance finalized, formal declaration expected soon.
title: Surpriya Sule plays badminton in unique election campaign
Shehbaz Sharif elected Pak PM for 2nd time
Greater Noida: 2 killed as mall ceiling grille collapses
Nasa shares picture of a natural phenomenon 'Cavum cloud'

description: UPI revolutionizes money transfers via payment apps, offering seamless and secure transactions. Change UPI ID on Google Pay by following simple steps. Create up to 4 IDs per bank account. Remove and re-add bank account to update on Google Pay.
title: How to change UPI ID on Google Pay: A step-by-step guide

description: Bill Gates visited India, including Microsoft India Development Centre, Bhubaneswar slums, and the Statue of Unity. He attended pre-wedding celebrations in Jamnagar. He also thanked Prime Minister Narendra Modi “for the invitation to visit this engineering marvel” and chief minister Bhupendrabhai Patel for hosting him. He discussed AI, DPI, and met with various ministers. He also shared a viral video with Dolly Chaiwala.
title: Watch: Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates visits world’s tallest statue
Pawan Singh says 'won't contest' after BJP names him Asansol pick

description: R Sai Kishore became the third bowler from Tamil Nadu to claim 50 wickets in a single Ranji Trophy season, achieving this during the semifinal clash against Mumbai. His impressive five-wicket haul dismantled the Mumbai middle-order on Day Two of the semifinal encounter. Despite a batting collapse on the opening day, Kishore's bowling performance turned the tide in his team's favor.
title: Watch: Sai Kishore grabs a fifer vs Mumbai in Ranji semi-final

description: Tejashwi Yadav criticizes Nitish Kumar for his changing stances; emphasizes consistency. Nitish Kumar assures PM Narendra Modi of commitment to BJP-led NDA after switching from INDIA bloc. Kumar forms grand alliance with RJD and Congress, becomes Chief Minister in 2015. In 2017, he severs ties with grand alliance due to corruption allegations and decline in governance.
title: At least this time Nitish should stick to his word, says Tejashwi

description: Discounts on Apple products, including iPhones, MacBooks, and AirPods. Lowest-ever prices and attractive discounts available. Flipkart offers a discount on 2nd-generation Apple AirPods and Apple iPhone 14. Croma provides a massive discount on MacBook Air M1. The Apple 20W fast charger is also available at a discounted price.
title: 3 not-to-miss Apple deals this week

description: Shah Rukh Khan wins the internet as he says 'Jai Shree Ram' on stage at the Ambanis' bash. He also danced on 'Naatu Naatu' with Salman Khan, Aamir Khan and Ram Charan
title: Shah Rukh begins speech with 'Jai Shree Ram' at pre-wedding bash

description: The wedding of Anant Ambani and Radhika Merchant in Jamnagar saw the presence of Rolls-Royce and BMWs, including the luxurious Rolls-Royce Ghost. Bollywood celebrities Shah Rukh Khan and Ranbir Kapoor arrived in style. The event also showcased the BMW iX electric SUV and a Range Rover SUV with a modern design and low aerodynamic resistance.
title: Exotic cars seen at Anant Ambani, Radhika Merchant's wedding

description: Shreyas Iyer, an out-of-favour India batter, failed to contribute with the bat in the Ranji Trophy semifinal match between Mumbai and Tamil Nadu. He was dismissed by Tamil Nadu pacer Sandeep Warrier for just 3 runs in their first innings. After Mumbai lost skipper Ajinkya Rahane after a 43-run partnership with Musheer Khan, Iyer couldn't stop the Tamil Nadu resurgence and was clean bowled by Warrier.
title: Shreyas Iyer out for 3 on his return to domestic cricket

description: Constable Ramesh Kurethi of Bastar Fighters was killed with a Naxalite in an encounter in Chhattisgarh's Kanker district. An AK-47 rifle was recovered from Hidur village, within Chhotebethiya police station's jurisdiction. The gunfight occurred in a forest during an anti-Naxal operation based on precise information. The official further informed that the search operations were underway.​​
title: Cop, Naxalite killed in encounter in Chhattsigarh's Kanker

description: Apple cancels smart car project. Govt approves semiconductor units. Google removes Indian apps. Sundar Pichai addresses errors. Phones witness price cut. Ashwini Vaishnaw highlights Assam unit. Cognizant asks employees to work from office. Pakistani hackers deface Burger Singh. Elon Musk contacts Satya Nadella. IBM asks for voluntary redundancy. Redmi 13C variant gets price cut.
title: Tata chip plant, Apple kills car project and other top tech news

description: Amidst the opulence of Anant Ambani and Radhika Merchant's lavish pre-wedding celebrations in Jamnagar, Smriti Irani and her husband Zubin attended in traditional elegance. The festivities included a jungle theme party, Mela Rouge, and a performance by Rihanna. The concluding day featured a Tusker Trails event and a Hastakshar event.
title: Smriti Irani attends Anant and Radhika's pre-wedding celebration

description: The current earnings season defied concerns about a decline in AI enthusiasm. The 'Magnificent Seven' tech giants, including Nvidia, Meta, and Microsoft, saw a 55% increase in earnings per share. The Nasdaq 100 reached a record high. Nvidia's earnings report caused a historic market value increase.
title: Rise of these 'magnificent 7' in tech shows AI is here to stay

description: Renowned Bhojpuri artist Pawan Singh, famous for his chart-topping album 'Lollipop Lagelu,' has been selected by the BJP as their candidate for the upcoming Lok Sabha elections in West Bengal's Asansol. This move sets the stage for an intriguing electoral battle, as Pawan Singh joins the political fray against another popular actor in the region. The BJP's decision to nominate Pawan is a strategic move aimed at garnering voter attention and securing vital constituencies in a state currently under the governance of Mamata Banerjee's Trinamool Congress (TMC).
title: Lollypop Lagelu Vs Khamosh? Pawan Singh is BJP’s pick for Asansol

description: Renowned Bhojpuri artist Pawan Singh, famous for his chart-topping album 'Lollipop Lagelu,' has been selected by the BJP as their candidate for the upcoming Lok Sabha elections in West Bengal's Asansol. This move sets the stage for an intriguing electoral battle, as Pawan Singh joins the political fray against another popular actor in the region. The BJP's decision to nominate Pawan is a strategic move aimed at garnering voter attention and securing vital constituencies in a state currently under the governance of Mamata Banerjee's Trinamool Congress (TMC).
title: Pawan Singh is BJP pick for Asansol: Who is the Bhojpuri singer

description: An Indian Navy seamen, Sahil Verma, has been reported missing from a naval ship since February 27. The Western Naval Command in Mumbai has launched a comprehensive search operation to locate him. A high-level board of inquiry has also been ordered to investigate the circumstances surrounding the incident. Updates will be provided as the investigation progresses.
title: Indian Navy launches search operation for missing sailor

description: Clad in traditional Indian attire, Dhoni and Bravo, former teammates for the Chennai Super Kings in the Indian Premier League, reveled in the festivities, joyously dancing to the rhythms of dandiya—a folk dance hailing from Gujarat—at a grand gala during the opulent three-day event.
title: Watch: Dhoni, Bravo groove in style playing dandiya

description: A class action lawsuit accuses Apple of rigging the competition by offering only iCloud for device backups. Users must pay for more storage, as rival platforms are restricted. Most users find 5GB insufficient.
title: Apple iCloud’s free tier may not be ‘enough’ for some users

description: Two Indian nationals, Santosh Goel and Sanjay Goel, were found dead in Abidjan. The Indian embassy is supporting the family and coordinating with local authorities for transportation of mortal remains. The embassy ensured full support to the family and the transportation of mortal remains. "We have strongly taken up the matter with the local authorities for thorough investigation," it said.
title: 2 Indians found dead in West Africa, embassy looking into matter

description: Spin legend Anil Kumble believes young wicketkeeper-batter Dhruv Jurel has the potential to achieve legendary skipper MS Dhoni's level in his career. Jurel made his debut in the third Test at Rajkot, delivering a knock of 46 and impressing in subsequent matches. Kumble praised Jurel's exceptional temperament in both defensive and attacking aspects of his game.
title: Kumble backs Dhruv Jurel to emulate Dhoni's success

description: Following Australia's victory over New Zealand in the Wellington Test, India ascended to the pinnacle of the World Test Championship (WTC) points table as per the latest update by the International Cricket Council (ICC) on Sunday. Their position atop can be further strengthened if they clinch victory in the upcoming fifth and final Test in Dharamsala, commencing on March 7.
title: India now No. 1 in World Test Championship table

description: Darjeeling BJP MLA Neeraj Zimba wrote a blood letter to PM Modi, reminding him of the unfulfilled pledge to grant Scheduled Tribe status to Gorkhas. He highlighted the neglect faced by Gorkhas and the issue of a separate state of Gorkhaland, opposed by TMC.
title: Darjeeling BJP MLA writes letter to PM in blood

description: Amarnath Ghosh's uncle is still unaware of the details of his nephew's death, four days after he was shot dead. The district police, administration, and various sources have not provided any information. Amarnath was a Kuchipudi and Bharatnatyam dance exponent from Suri in Bengal's Birbhum district. The incident came in spotlight when TV actor  Devoleena Bhattacharjee took her X to post about this information.
title: 'No one left...': Uncle of Indian dancer shot dead in US

description: During a tiger-herbivore census in North Bengal's Buxa Tiger Reserve, a forest guard named Ali Miyan was trampled to death by an elephant in the Pukhri area of Jayanti range due to his gun failure. The incident caused discontent among the villagers and resulted in a mob attack.
title: Gun fails to fire, elephant kills forest guard during census

description: Rajeev Chandrasekhar, a former minister, is set to challenge Congress heavyweight Shashi Tharoor in the Lok Sabha elections from Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala. Chandrasekhar's journey includes founding BPL Mobile and Jupiter Capital. He has been a leading voice within the Modi government and actively participates in key committees.
title: Clash of titans looming in Kerala state capital?

description: Rajeev Chandrasekhar, a former minister, is set to challenge Congress heavyweight Shashi Tharoor in the Lok Sabha elections from Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala. Chandrasekhar's journey includes founding BPL Mobile and Jupiter Capital. He has been a leading voice within the Modi government and actively participates in key committees.
title: Clash of titans looming in Kerala state capital?

description: IMD data shows 540 districts in India experiencing water stress and dry conditions, with 98 facing extreme to severe to moderately dry conditions. The early onset of dry conditions is concerning, with higher evaporation rates expected due to above-normal temperatures. Pre-monsoon rainfall is crucial to alleviate the dryness and prevent further impact on agriculture, dam, and canal water levels.
title: 540 dists across India already under water stress: IMD data

description: Rashtriya Lok Dal joins NDA after Jayant Chaudhary meets Amit Shah and JP Nadda. Shah welcomes Jayant, expresses confidence in PM's policies. RLD MLAs voted for BJP. RLD joins NDA for development and welfare. Nadda says 'Abki Baar 400 paar' on X.
title: RLD formally joins NDA after Jayant meets Shah, Nadda

description: Umashankar Singh's decision to vote for Sanjay Seth in Rajya Sabha polls fuels opposition claims of BSP working with BJP. Mayawati's lack of reaction shows party support. Akash Anand, Mayawati's nephew and political successor, receives Y-plus category security amid his Lok Sabha campaign. He aims to motivate youth, collect data on Dalit voters, and expand BSP's influence in other states.
title: Y-plus security for Mayawati's heir Akash Anand

description: Sunil Gavaskar compared wicketkeeper-batter Dhruv Jurel to MS Dhoni, highlighting the youngster's impressive performance in India's fourth Test against England in Ranchi. Jurel's crucial knock of 90 in the first innings helped India reach England's total. Gavaskar drew parallels between the young talent and Dhoni, stating that he was "another MS Dhoni in the making."
title: 'There is only one...': Gavaskar clarifies Jurel-Dhoni comparison

description: BJP fields experienced leader Shivraj Singh Chouhan from Vidisha, raising questions about his role in Delhi. With extensive political experience, including being a 5-term Lok Sabha MP and longest-serving CM, Chouhan's potential role in the org or govt is being discussed.
title: Call for BJP’s CM with longest tenure Shivraj to return

description: A significant number of patients in Kolkata suffer from 'internet-mediated fear of death' or cyberchondria. They believe they are ill even after seeking medical help and getting cured because they trust internet information more than doctors. Patients need to understand that treatment can cure them and should limit their internet research before consulting a doctor.
title: Doctors impatient on internet knowledge over medical advice

description: Oppo recently launched the Oppo F25 Pro, its slimmest F-series smartphone in India. The mid-range smartphone features an IP68 rating, octa-core MediaTek chipset, 8GB of RAM, and a 6.7-inch full HD+ AMOLED display. It runs on Android 14 and has a triple rear camera setup, including a 64MP main sensor and a 32MP front camera.
title: Oppo F25 Pro vs Realme 12 Pro: Two mid-range smartphones comparison

description: Nvidia CEO predicts AGI in 5 years, based on definition. AGI possesses human-like intelligence and cognitive abilities. More chip factories are needed to support the growth of the AI industry. Defined goals and improving chip efficiency are crucial for AGI. Huang also noted that there is a need for more chip factories to support the AI industry's growth.
title: What Nvidia CEO has to say on human-level AI becoming a reality

description: Google's AI platform faces controversy as IT minister Rajeev Chandrasekhar emphasizes government approval and labeling of under-trial AI models. Platforms must seek user consent and ensure safety on the Indian public internet, or face penal consequences. The advisory asks the entities to seek approval from the government for deploying under trial or unreliable artificial intelligence (AI) models.
title: Govt to tech cos: Take permission before launching AI models in India

description: Customizing an Android phone's lock screen is crucial in reflecting personal style. Users can personalize it with widgets, unique clock styles, and dynamic wallpapers. Glance Smart Lock Screen offers personalized content. Customized notifications and shortcuts enhance the user experience while privacy should be maintained.
title: 6 tips to keep in mind while customising your Android lock screen

description: Inter Miami defeated Orlando City 5-0 in Major League Soccer, thanks to Lionel Messi and Luis Suarez's impressive performances. Orlando, who finished second in the Eastern Conference last season, was unable to match their superior opponents. Miami now have seven points from their first three games, marking a strong start to the season.
title: Messi, Suarez score twice as Miami crush Orlando 5-0

description: A Mercedes driver crashed his SUV into a scooter, killing the rider and injuring a pedestrian. The driver fled the scene, leaving behind the car. The incident has been reported to the police. Rakesh Verma, a resident of Subhash Nagar, was killed in the accident.
title: Man going to do yoga dies as Merc crashes into his scooter

description: A 55-year-old salesman was arrested in Ghaziabad for killing his wife and staying in their one-room house. The neighbors alerted the police due to a foul smell. The couple had frequent quarrels, and the salesman provided financial support to his first wife. A postmortem examination was conducted, and an FIR was registered.
title: Man kills wife, locks himself up in house with body for 3 days

description: Nathan Lyon took six wickets for 65 runs in the first Test against New Zealand, which resulted in Australia registering a 172-run victory. This victory gave Australia a 1-0 lead in the series. Cameron Green's unbeaten knock of 174 in the first innings was the difference-maker. The second and final match will be held in Christchurch on Friday.
title: 1st Test: Lyon shines as Australia thrash NZ by 172 runs

description: Calcutta High Court judge found the word 'darling' to be an offensive and sexually coloured remark in an appeal case. Former advocate general of Bengal believed a simple warning would have sufficed. Psychologist stated that 'darling' has a sexual connotation in a special relationship.
title: Calling unknown woman 'darling' offensive: HC

description: Residents of Ajronda village in Faridabad found the body of a newborn impaled on a fence with iron spikes. The baby was suspected to be thrown over the fence from Officer's Colony. Police are investigating the incident and have registered an FIR.
title: Newborn found impaled by spikes in Haryana, cops 'know who did it'

description: The chief minister of Hyderabad is working towards developing the city's night economy by merging municipalities, implementing supportive bylaws, and improving transportation facilities. This aims to boost economic growth, increase tax revenues, and create better employment opportunities.
title: Telangana govt pushes for 24x7 'night economy' in Hyderabad

description: BJP has fielded Kompella Madhavi Latha, a woman who has campaigned against triple talaq, as its candidate against AIMIM chief Asaduddin Owaisi for the Hyderabad Lok Sabha seat. The party has not named its sitting Adilabad MP, Soyam Bapu Rao yet.
title: It's triple talaq campaigner vs Asaduddin Owaisi in Hyderabad

description: The debate over the significance of Ranji Trophy in Indian cricket continues, with the focus of the BCCI Selection Committee considerably also on IPL performances for picking the Indian teams. However, former players like Devang Gandhi and Sunil Subramaniam argue that Ranji Trophy performances should be prioritized for Test team selections.
title: Ranji Trophy vs IPL: Which way do selectors sway?

description: A Spanish tourist was allegedly gang-raped and her husband brutally assaulted in Kurumahat, Jharkhand. The police detained three persons and formed a special investigation team. The survivor shared their ordeal on Instagram. The incident was condemned by both the governing and opposition camps in Jharkhand assembly.
title: Spanish tourist on bike tour in Jharkhand raped by 7, police arrest 4
